A few original combinations worth exploring

Here are some combinations that I think have interesting potential:

1. Delta Market
Every action creates measurable deltas. Rewards depend on the magnitude and durability of positive state change, not raw activity.

2. Invariant Hunter
Points are awarded for discovering principles that continue to work after changing domains or representations.

3. Constraint Forge
Instead of collecting items, players collect constraints. New constraints unlock new solution spaces rather than restricting play.

4. Resolution Economy
Zooming in costs resources. Zooming out loses detail. The strategy is deciding the right resolution for each problem.

5. Counterfactual Branching
Any major decision can spawn an alternate branch for exploration. Later, branches can merge by importing only validated insights.

6. Observer Gain
Simply observing a system at higher quality reveals hidden mechanics. Better observation—not stronger actions—is the upgrade path.

7. Compression Score
A solution is rewarded not just for working, but for explaining the most phenomena with the fewest principles.

